	<p>Hello,
I'm a student of Bangladesh University of Engineering and Technology, from Bangladesh. Students around the country demand the reformation of the Quota allocations provided during recruitment of officers for various public services in Bangladesh. Currently, 30% of the recruitments are allotted to descendants of freedom fighters, 10% of the seats go to applicants from different districts, 10% of the seats go to women, and 5% go to ethnic minorities, and 1% go to differenty abled people, leaving the general population to compete for only 44% of the seats. The whole country's students have been involved in non-violent movements for quite some time now but were brutally attacked by the police force yesterday night.The government already exercises vast control over our national media, thus rendering a lot of grim stories untold. As such, we seek the help of foreign media to cover the true brutality of what is going on in our campus, our university. Please do come forward, as the situation is beyond our control. 
We need you.
#BBC #CNN #ReformQuotaBD
